# Agent Orchestration Decisions Log

Append-only audit trail for non-trivial orchestration decisions made during
agent-team work. Required by [`docs/references/multi-agent.md`](../docs/references/multi-agent.md) §8.3
("Sonnet orchestrator fallback mode"): when Opus is unavailable, every
deferred or risky decision must be recorded here so Opus can review on return.

## When to write an entry

- Sonnet (or any sub-agent) is acting as fallback orchestrator and makes a
  decision normally reserved for Opus (architecture, schema, external API
  contract, security).
- A `status: partial` was accepted and the unresolved part was deferred.
- A risky routing call was overridden against the matrix
  (e.g. skipped `codex` review for time pressure).
- An agent's auto-classifier or permission system blocked a step and the
  user manually unblocked it — the trail matters.

Do NOT log every routine call here — those go to `.claude/agent-log.jsonl`
via the PreToolUse hook. This file is for *decisions worth reviewing*.

## Entry format (one block per entry, blank line between blocks)

```
ts:       <ISO timestamp>
mode:     opus | sonnet-fallback | other
decided:  <one-line headline>
why:      <reasoning, multi-line OK>
by:       main | <agent-id>
revisit:  Y | N    # Y means "review when Opus returns"
links:    [optional] file paths, PR/issue links, commit SHAs
```

## Review cadence

- Quarterly: `python3 scripts/agent_stats.py --since <date>` + walk this log,
  cross-check against [`docs/references/agent-teams.md`](../docs/references/agent-teams.md) §2 routing matrix.
- After Opus absence ends: walk all `revisit: Y` entries, decide accept / revise / revert.

